name: pycbc
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "PyCBC" %}
{% set version = "2.0.4" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f1899f46e55a7171d1a6d82a4f0157282daa93e9230c02c903f81f58388a3bed
  patches:
    # skip regenerating the git_version_info
    # https://github.com/gwastro/pycbc/issues/3917
    - skip-generate_git_version_info.patch
    # remove lalsuite requirement from python metadata
    - no-install_requires-lalsuite.patch
    # enable openmp on all platforms
    - openmp-macos.patch

build:
  error_overdepending: true
  error_overlinking: true
  ignore_run_exports:
    # not sure why, on osx-arm64 libcxx isn't
    # linked in the compiled extension modules
    - libcxx  # [osx and arm64]
    # not directly linked
    - numpy
    - python
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [win]
  script:
    - export CFLAGS="${CFLAGS} -fopenmp"  # [osx]
    - {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
  host:
    - cython
    - libgomp  # [linux]
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - numpy
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - astropy !=4.0.5,!=4.2.1,>=2.0.3
    - beautifulsoup4 >=4.6.0
    - cython >=0.29
    - decorator >=3.4.2
    - dqsegdb
    - dqsegdb2 >=1.0.1
    - gwdatafind
    - h5py >=2.10
    - jinja2
    - ligo-gracedb
    - ligo-segments
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - lscsoft-glue >=1.59.3
    - mako >=1.0.1
    - matplotlib-base >=2.0.0
    - mpld3 >=0.3
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - numpy !=1.19.0
    - pegasus-wms.api >=5.0.1
    - pkg-config
    - pillow
    - python
    - python-lalframe
    - python-lalsimulation
    - requests >=1.2.1
    - scipy >=0.16.0
    - six >=1.10.0
    - tqdm
  run_constrained:
    # https://github.com/gwastro/pycbc/pull/3901#issuecomment-993519319
    - liblalmetaio !=2.1.0

test:
  imports:
    - pycbc
    - pycbc.bin_utils

    - pycbc.conversions

about:
  home: https://pycbc.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/gwastro/pycbc/
  doc_url: http://pycbc.org/pycbc/latest/html/
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Core library to analyze gravitational-wave data, find signals, and study their parameters.
  description: |
    PyCBC is a software package used to explore astrophysical sources
    of gravitational waves.
    It contains algorithms that can detect coalescing compact binaries
    and measure the astrophysical parameters of detected sources.
    PyCBC was used in the first direct detection of gravitational
    waves (GW150914) by LIGO and is used in the ongoing analysis of
    LIGO and Virgo data.

extra:

    - duncanmmacleod
    - ahnitz
